<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3789] Node.js lacks ability to destroy connection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3789</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;At present, there is no means for destroying the socket underlying a Node.js Thrift Connection. When using TLS, If the socket fails to connect, calling end() is insufficient to release its resources. (end() sends a FIN packet, which is never acknowledged, holding the socket open.) This unreleased socket will prevent Node.js from exiting cleanly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12959772">THRIFT-3789</key>
            <summary>Node.js lacks ability to destroy connection</summary>
