&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3789&quot; title=&quot;Node.js lacks ability to destroy connection&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3789&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3789&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Add `destroy` to Connection instance&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This commit proxies the `destroy` method from the Thrift Connection&lt;br/&gt;
    object to its underlying socket, akin to the existing `end` method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Without `destroy`, it&apos;s possible for a failed TLS socket to hold the&lt;br/&gt;
    Node.js process open. (Calling `end` is not sufficient to close the OS&lt;br/&gt;
    handle because `end` sends a FIN packet, which is never acknowledged by&lt;br/&gt;
    the server.)&lt;/p&gt;

